1 3. Joint integrity and alignment; and
2 4. Absence of significant defects such as cracks, deformations,
3 or separations.
4 C. The contractor shall bear the cost of the post-installation
5 inspection and any corrective measures required to meet the
6 Departmentâ€™s standards. If a storm pipe fails the post-installation
7 inspection, the contractor shall take corrective action, which may
8 include removal and replacement, reinforcement, or other remediation
9 as directed by the Department.
10 D. The Oklahoma Department of Transportation shall promulgate
11 rules necessary to implement and enforce the provisions of this
12 section, including, but not limited to, specifications for
13 inspections, testing protocols, and qualifications for inspectors.
14 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
